education</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The academies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and free schools programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> embody</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that trend, giving scho</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ols </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">greater autonomy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, within a strong framework of accountability. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">For the vast majority of academies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and free schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> this autonomy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> giving them </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">space, the opportunity, and most importantly the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">confidence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to innovate and improve. These improvements are reflected in their results.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academies are spearheading p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">artnership</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and new forms of collaboration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">playing a key role in driving forward improvem</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ents in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We believe the education </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">experts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> know best</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">But</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">here failure is evident</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it will not be tolerated. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We will take swift, robust action against signs of underperformance. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As numbers grow we must take decisions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">about</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> how </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">best to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">safeguard this autonomy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> whilst providing support for those who need it. We will be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">giving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> power to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">School </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commissioners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, to ensure decisions are taken by those with a real understanding of what will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">work locally</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 56.7pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">International evidence shows that greater autonomy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">drives up educational standards, and is most effective when coupled with accountability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">School autonomy is a key feature of high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">performing education systems. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Organisation for Economic Co-operation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and Development’s (OECD)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">study “PISA in Focus” (2011)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">stated: “At the country level , the greater the number of schools that have the responsibility to define and elaborate their own curricula and assessments, the better the performance of the whole system</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, even after accounting for national income.” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Japan, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Korea, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Netherlands, Macao-China and Hong Kong-China, all high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">performing education systems, have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">high</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">levels of school autonomy</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Autonomy driven from the bottom up is better than state</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">led</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> policies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Charter schools in the USA have been successful due to the freedom they have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to adopt best practice</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> raise sta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ndards</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. They show that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in New York charter schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> “frequent teacher feedback, data-driven instruction, high-dosage tutoring, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increased ins</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tructional time, and a relentless focus on academic achievement explains roughly half of the variation in school effectiveness.” </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.01pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Giving schools the freedom to adopt best practice helps narrow the attainment gap for disadvantaged students.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Hoxby</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> et al</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (20</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">09)</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> shows that charter schools in New York close the gap separating inner-city neighbourhood students from those of the wealthiest suburbs (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Scarsdale-Harlem Achievement Gap) – by 86</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in maths and 66</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in English. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">utonomous schools do not just improve in isolation. Studies by Bettinger (2005)</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, Hoxby (2002)</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and Booker et al (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">200</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">8</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> show that the improved performance of autonomous schools can improve the quality of schools in the neighbouring area. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Autonomy is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">mos</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t effective when</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> supported by a robust accountability framework.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">“PISA Results in Focus” (2013)</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">found </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">that autonomous </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> “perform better than schools with less autonomy when they are part of school systems wi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">th more accountability arrangements.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">“E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ducation at a Glance” (2010)</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, found autonomous schools achieve PISA scores in science that are 46 PISA scale points higher than where schools lack such autonomy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> or as much as 63 points </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">higher </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">where autonomy is accompanied </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> strong accountability</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. These </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are big gains – 63 PISA points is equivalent to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a student’s achievement rising, across their qualifications, by around 11 GCSE grades.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Autonomy and accountabi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">lity are the two key pillars of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">academies reform</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academies and free schools </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> take decisions on how best to raise standards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and are free to bring in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new expertise </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to help run their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academies have</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">better governance arrangements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academy Trust members</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> have control </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of their </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">budgets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are free</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to set their own curriculum</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">; can </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hoose the best teachers based on merit, rather than being tied to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">q</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ualified </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eacher </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">tatus;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reward </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">these </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">teachers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> they see fit.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">But these freedoms are granted within a robust accountability system. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We have toughened accountability for all schools. But </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cademies and free schools are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">subject to a higher level of scrutiny</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> through the rigour and transparency of their governance arrangements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academy trusts must adhere to their funding agreement and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he academies financial handbook,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">produce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> annual accounts for scrutiny by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">an independent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">external auditor.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Audited a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ccounts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and funding agreement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are published</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as are details of budget allocations to academies.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In LA-maintained schools it is the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">local authority that has responsibility for financial oversight. The frequency and depth of audit is variable and maintained schools are often not subject to the same rigo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r as academies and free schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">There is a distinct appetite for autonomy in Engl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">and, evident in all types of school.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2010</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> we have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">had</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> overwhelming interest from parents, community members, businesses and individuals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> wanting the opportunity to create new, innovative </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">free </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are 174 open free schools, which will provide nearly 82,000 places when full. A further 115 schools are in the pipeline and many more are applying. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There has also been significant demand from teachers and governors to run their own </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Since 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">010</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2,573</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">converted</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> become academies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with another 510</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in the pipeline</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Academy status is not just for one type of school. Initially there was more i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nterest from secondary schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">; secondary schools typically have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">more</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">operational respon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sibility</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> than primary schools</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">often </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a school business manager</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in control of a considerably bigger budget</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-siz