, 41</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of which have b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">een in this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> category</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> more than 18 months. S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ince </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2007</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 56 LAs have not issued a single warning notice, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">despite individual school underperformance in their area.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="51" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Where LAs have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">intervened</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in failing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">schools that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> action has not been of sufficient standard. One in three LA</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">driven action plans </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> considered to be of too poor a standard to secure the necessary </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">improvements</span><a name="_ftnref20"></a><a href="#_ftn20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="52" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> reaction to financial failure is equally unimpressive. The EFA </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">found</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in early 2013</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> there were seven local authorities with at least three schools </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">each </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which had been</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in deficit continually for five years</span><a name="_ftnref21"></a><a href="#_ftn21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. Some of these deficits amounted to well over 10% of the school’s annual revenue and, in a minority of cases, over 25%.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="53" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">To dither</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and not take effective action</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in the face of failure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-s