yle="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">whilst enabling </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">academies to continue to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> enjoy the autonomy that is so critical to t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">heir success.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.3pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:right; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">12</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> OECD (2013) - </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">PISA 2012 Results: What Makes Schools Successful? Resources, Policies and Practices (Volume IV)</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Dobbie</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> W., and Fryer R. (2011) Getting Beneath the Veil of Effective Schools: Evidence from New York City. NBER Working Papers, No. 7632</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Hoxby, C.M., Murarka, S., and Kang, J</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><span s